# OpenSim Python API Rules

## Verified API (OpenSim 4.5+)
Use ONLY these verified class/method names. Do not guess — hallucinated names fail silently.

```python
import opensim
model = opensim.Model(str(model_path))
model.initSystem()
ik_tool = opensim.InverseKinematicsTool()
ik_tool.setModel(model)
ik_tool.set_output_motion_file(str(out_mot))
ik_tool.setStartTime(t_start)
ik_tool.setEndTime(t_end)
ik_tool.run()
analyze_tool = opensim.AnalyzeTool(str(setup_xml_path))
analyze_tool.run()
muscle_set = model.getMuscles()
muscle_names = [muscle_set.get(i).getName() for i in range(muscle_set.getSize())]
storage = opensim.Storage(str(sto_path))
```

## XML Setup Files
Generate setup XMLs programmatically with xml.etree.ElementTree from templates in src/templates/.
Never hardcode XML strings inline in Python.

## dry_run Mode
Every public function in opensim_pipeline.py must support dry_run: bool = False.
When dry_run=True: skip opensim calls, return np.random.rand(T, N).astype(np.float32).

## Error Handling
Wrap every .run() call in try/except.
Log opensim error reporter output at ERROR level.
Raise RuntimeError with sequence ID and stage name on failure.

## Temp Files
All intermediate files go to config['paths']['temp_dir'] / sequence_id /.
Delete on success. Keep on failure for debugging.
